headline: Amazon’s Satellite Internet Venture Signs Up Its First Airline. Here’s What We Know.
summary: Amazon  satellite arm has struck a deal with a major U.S. airline in what is a first for the company.  Amazon  said in a press release Thursday that  JetBlue  will use Project Kuiper, its low Earth orbit satellite network, to enhance free on-flight Wi-Fi.  The service will be implemented on select flights starting in 2027, Amazon said.
